<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="518" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">211.65/103: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-10T16:00:00-05:00">April 10, 1934—4
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>27. Your 56, April 9, Noon. Pending receipt of further instructions
                                following arrival of Italian draft treaty you may withhold action on
                                Department’s 24, April 5, 1 P.M.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>